description:
&lt;p&gt;8A Matron – Trauma Orthopaedics &amp; Plastics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about leading and developing your team to facilitate and maintain high quality patient care? Is making a difference and doing the right thing fundamental to you? Is facilitating excellent nursing care and getting the basics right one of your key drivers?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great Matrons have a strong sense of ownership of their wards and they excel to high standards. They thrive on the business of their environment, model strengths and motivators and are passionate for both patient outcomes and their team’s development and wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Valentine Ellis Ward is a fast paced 25 bedded acute Trauma, Orthopaedic and Plastics Ward and also works closely with our Major Trauma Centre to provide step down care for patients following neuro and spinal trauma.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the nature of this busy environment and current climate, the job can at times be challenging but for the right person this is a very rewarding role. Ideally this would not be your first ward management role but this is not ruled out for the right candidate. If you feel you have the right skills and attributes then we would encourage your application. Informal visits are strongly encouraged for all shortlisted candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like the role for you then we’d love to hear from you. Please contact Petrina Quirke, Lead Nurse at Petrina.quirke@nhs.net in the first instance to arrange an informal discussion regarding this opportunity. We look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
